  "text": "The primary source of audit log entries for authorization decisions in Apache Kafka is the StandardAuthorizerData class located at metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizerData.java. This class implements audit logging for ACL authorization decisions with the following mechanism:\n\n1. The StandardAuthorizerData class contains an auditLog logger obtained from LoggerFactory.getLogger(\"kafka.authorizer.logger\") at line 115-116.\n\n2. The authorize() method (line 228-252) handles authorization decisions and calls logAuditMessage() (line 250) which logs all authorization events.\n\n3. The logAuditMessage() method (lines 281-310) logs authorization decisions based on the result:\n   - For ALLOWED results (lines 288-297): Logs at DEBUG level when action.logIfAllowed() is true, otherwise at TRACE level\n   - For DENIED results (lines 299-309): Logs at INFO level when action.logIfDenied() is true, otherwise at TRACE level\n\n4. The buildAuditMessage() method (lines 254-271) constructs detailed audit messages containing:\n   - Principal identity\n   - Authorization result (Allowed/Denied)\n   - Operation type\n   - Client host\n   - Resource pattern\n   - Request type\n   - Resource reference count\n   - Matching ACL rule details\n\nThe StandardAuthorizer class (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizer.java) serves as the main authorizer implementation that delegates authorization to StandardAuthorizerData and also records authorization metrics.\n\nThe audit logging infrastructure is integrated with the Action class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/Action.java) which provides logIfAllowed() and logIfDenied() flags to control whether specific authorization decisions should be logged based on the context of the authorization request."
}

